title: Layout Constraints & Scroll Lock Rules
scope: All screens in Book A Dink (SwiftUI iOS)
applies_to: Claude Code sessions, code review, new feature work
---

## Core Principle

The app must ALWAYS be locked to viewport width.
No screen may allow horizontal scrolling or dragging under any circumstance.


## Root Cause (Historical Bug — GameDetailView, April 2026)

A child HStack (`largeAvatarRow`) contained up to 7 fixed-size circles at 44pt each
with 8pt spacing = 356pt. Available card width on a standard iPhone was 318pt.

The parent card VStack had no `.frame(maxWidth: .infinity)` modifier, so it reported
its intrinsic content width (oversized) upward. The body VStack adopted that width.
The outer `ScrollView(.vertical)` had no explicit width constraint on its content.

Result: the entire screen became horizontally draggable.

Fix: two changes.
1. Added `.frame(maxWidth: .infinity)` to `playersCard` and `venueInfoCard`.
2. Reduced `largeAvatarRow` from `prefix(6)` to `prefix(4)` so max row width = 252pt.


## Non-Negotiable Rules

**Rule 1 — Root container must constrain width.**
Every screen body VStack (direct child of ScrollView) must carry:
    .frame(maxWidth: .infinity)
or:
    .frame(maxWidth: .infinity, alignment: .leading)

Do NOT remove or weaken this modifier.

**Rule 2 — Every card/section component must constrain width.**
Any view that is a card (has a background, overlay, or shadow) must have
`.frame(maxWidth: .infinity)` as its outermost size modifier, before `.background(...)`.

Pattern (correct):
    VStack(...) { ... }
        .frame(maxWidth: .infinity)          // ← MUST be first
        .background(..., in: RoundedRectangle(...))
        .overlay(...)
        .shadow(...)

Pattern (wrong — card adopts intrinsic content width):
    VStack(...) { ... }
        .background(..., in: RoundedRectangle(...))

**Rule 3 — Never use `.fixedSize(horizontal: true)`.**
This instructs SwiftUI to ignore the proposed width and use intrinsic width instead.
It will cause overflow if the intrinsic width exceeds the viewport.

Allowed: `.fixedSize(horizontal: false, vertical: true)` — this only expands height.
Allowed: `.fixedSize()` on small contained elements (badges, labels) inside already-constrained parents.

**Rule 4 — No unbounded fixed-width HStacks.**
Any HStack whose children have explicit `.frame(width: X)` modifiers must satisfy:
    sum(child widths) + sum(spacing) < (screen width − horizontal padding)

Minimum screen width to target: 375pt (iPhone SE).
Standard body padding: 20pt each side = 40pt total.
Standard card inner padding: 16pt each side = 32pt total.
Available card content width on SE: 375 − 40 − 32 = 303pt.

If a row cannot satisfy this with N items, cap with `prefix(N)` and show a `+X` badge.

**Rule 5 — No explicit `minWidth` or forced width on containers.**
Do not use `frame(minWidth: X)` on any container view unless tightly bounded and
the minWidth is smaller than the viewport content width.

**Rule 6 — GeometryReader must NEVER feed oversized widths back into layout.**
If GeometryReader is used, only read its value for positioning/offsets.
Do NOT set a child's `.frame(width: geometry.size.width + constant)` or similar.

**Rule 7 — Horizontal ScrollViews are banned inside vertical page screens.**
Do not add `ScrollView(.horizontal)` inside any full-page vertical scroll unless it is
a dedicated carousel component that is explicitly width-bounded and documented.


## Avatar / Row Constraints

- Avatar preview rows must always be capped with `prefix(N)`.
- Remaining items must be shown as a `+N` badge, never as additional circles.
- The cap `N` must satisfy: `(N+1) × 44 + N × 8 ≤ availableCardWidth`.
- Current cap: `prefix(4)` → max 5 items = 252pt (fits in 303pt on SE with 51pt margin).
- If avatar size or card padding changes, recalculate and update the cap.


## Validation Checklist (Run Before Merging Any GameDetailView or Layout Change)

Test states:
- [ ] 0 registered players
- [ ] 1 registered player
- [ ] 11+ registered players (triggers avatar cap and +N badge)
- [ ] Long game title (30+ characters)
- [ ] Long venue name
- [ ] Small device: iPhone SE (375pt) or simulator equivalent

Confirm:
- [ ] Screen cannot be dragged horizontally in ANY of the above states
- [ ] `+N` badge appears correctly when attendees exceed prefix cap
- [ ] Summary line still shows correct total count
- [ ] No card is clipped unexpectedly
- [ ] Expanded players list scrolls vertically, not horizontally


